        <num>CC 1467</num>
        <heading>DONATIONS</heading>
        <content>
          <p>TITLE II.  DONATIONS
CHAPTER 1.  GENERAL DISPOSITIONS
Art. 1467.  Methods of acquiring or disposing gratuitously
Property can neither be acquired nor disposed of gratuitously except by donations inter vivos or mortis causa, made in one of the forms hereafter established.</p>
        </content>
